Spain May Reduce Purchases of Combat Equipment, El Pais Reports

-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 
2011-10-12T06:05:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/spain-may-reduce-purchases-of-combat-equipment-el-pais-reports.html
Spain  is reviewing plans to buy
combat equipment as it seeks to reduce weapons spending by at
least 5.2 billion euros ($7.1 billion), El Pais reported, citing
a Defense Ministry report to the parliament.  The country may cut purchases of Eurofighter combat planes,
NH-90 helicopters or Leopard tanks, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
 eduarterubia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
